title.narrative: CHILD RIGHTS MONITORING AND FINANCING OF SOCIAL SERVICES FOR CHILDREN

description.narrative: By 2022, national capacities to develop, manage and use child rights monitoring data to understand the situation of children including children with disabilities in Myanmar strengthened., which contributes to Cross-Sectoral - Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses, Cross-Sectoral - Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses (Covid), Evaluation, Evaluation (Covid), Operations Support To Programme Delivery, Reducing Child Poverty, Research. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Improved policy environment, budgets and systems for all children, especially the most excluded, guided by improved knowledge and disaggregated data
